1) The MATLAB code can be execute in MATLAB. No additional code needed.
2) For the Julia code, proceed as follows:
  - Download Julia 1.11 from http://julialang.org/downloads/
  - Start Julia
  - Install the four packages: PyPlot, DataStructures, RandomNumbers, StatsBase by first pressing "]" and then executing the command add PyPlot, FFTW, Statistics
  - Load the code: `include("OrientationMapsJulia07.jl")`
  - End run it: `close("all");@time lrim(10^6,0.98,1.7)` â€” This will produce the output, and some stats.
